Control Which HTTP Status Codes Refresh Access Tokens for Named Credentials

You can now account for external systems that return non-standard HTTP status codes when callouts from Salesforce use invalid or expired credentials. In addition to the standard 401 response, you can specify other 4xx HTTP status codes so that Salesforce can refresh access tokens when the external system returns these codes.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in all editions.

How: From Setup, enter Named Credentials, select Named Credentials, create or edit an external credential, and in the Additional Status Codes for Token Refresh field, enter 4xx status codes.
title: Control HTTP Status Codes for Named Credentials
